title: [Feywrot Mire, Highland]
description: A tangle of twisted trunks with smooth, light grey bark mark the stands of wax myrtles along the pathway.  Their aromatic olive green leaves lend a pleasant fragrance to the area and the pale blue berries have attracted numerous wildfowl, judging by the variety of feathers scarttered beneath the thicket.
